					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You can see the benefits of giving similarly colored areas their own palette (less banding, better textures, etc.), but the edges where different palettes meet is indeed atrocious. Maybe what we need is to analyze the tiles where different palettes touch so we can force a few colors from one palette into the other. This would make things significantly more complicated.</div>

