				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Dithering causes problems no matter the pattern, if the color difference is too high then it'll result in severe artifacts, period.<br /><br />The biggest problem with checkerboard dithering is its notorious tendency to wreck the silhouettes. Vertical dithering was used in large part to reduce the effects from this, not to reduce the amount of artifacts (if anything, they're made worse).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

